&lt;Avana Group Plc>, defending itselfagainst a bid from Ranks Hovis McDougall Plc &lt;RHML.L>, RHM,forecast a 3.4 mln stg rise in profits in the 1986/87 year.    It said pretax profit should rise to 23.0 mln stg in theyear to April 2, 1987 from 19.6 mln previously, and reach 27.5mln in 1987/88. It expects share earnings to rise to 46.9p from38.7p and to 51.2p in 1987/88, and the 1986/87 dividend to be17.0p net, a 41.6 pct increase.    The bid from RHM, rejected by the food and bakery group, isworth about 270 mln stg. RHM currently has a 22.9 pct stake inpurchases and acceptances. REUTER&#3;